BURNSVILLE, Minn.  â€” U.S. Rep. Angie Craig is officially announcing she will run for reelection this fall. Craig issued a statement Sunday saying enthusiasm for her campaign is strong. Craig was first elected to Congress in 2018. She represents Minnesota's 2nd Congressional District, which includes the Twin Cities' far southeastern suburbs and rural parts of southeastern Minnesota. Republican Tyler Kistner is running for the seat. Craig narrowly defeated him in 2020.